Note: Reduction functions
Process called "sum" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and dtype as Optional[NDArray.DataType] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let target_dtype be dtype or a.dtype
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Return NDArray.sum with array as a and axis as axis and dtype as target_dtype and keepdims as keep_dimensions

Process called "prod" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and dtype as Optional[NDArray.DataType] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let target_dtype be dtype or a.dtype
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Return NDArray.prod with array as a and axis as axis and dtype as target_dtype and keepdims as keep_dimensions

Process called "mean" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and dtype as Optional[NDArray.DataType] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let target_dtype be dtype or NDArray.Float64
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Return NDArray.mean with array as a and axis as axis and dtype as target_dtype and keepdims as keep_dimensions

Process called "std" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and dtype as Optional[NDArray.DataType] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] and ddof as Optional[Integer] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let target_dtype be dtype or NDArray.Float64
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Let delta_dof be ddof or 0
    Return NDArray.std with array as a and axis as axis and dtype as target_dtype and keepdims as keep_dimensions and ddof as delta_dof

Process called "var" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and dtype as Optional[NDArray.DataType] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] and ddof as Optional[Integer] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let target_dtype be dtype or NDArray.Float64
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Let delta_dof be ddof or 0
    Return NDArray.var with array as a and axis as axis and dtype as target_dtype and keepdims as keep_dimensions and ddof as delta_dof

Process called "min" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Return NDArray.min with array as a and axis as axis and keepdims as keep_dimensions

Process called "max" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Return NDArray.max with array as a and axis as axis and keepdims as keep_dimensions

Process called "argmin" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return NDArray.argmin with array as a and axis as axis

Process called "argmax" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return NDArray.argmax with array as a and axis as axis

Process called "all" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Return NDArray.all with array as a and axis as axis and keepdims as keep_dimensions

Process called "any" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and keepdims as Optional[Boolean] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let keep_dimensions be keepdims or false
    Return NDArray.any with array as a and axis as axis and keepdims as keep_dimensions

Note: Sorting and searching
Process called "sort" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and kind as Optional[String] and order as Optional[String] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let sort_axis be axis or -1
    Let sort_kind be kind or "quicksort"
    Return NDArray.sort with array as a and axis as sort_axis and kind as sort_kind

Process called "argsort" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and kind as Optional[String] and order as Optional[String] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let sort_axis be axis or -1
    Let sort_kind be kind or "quicksort"
    Return NDArray.argsort with array as a and axis as sort_axis and kind as sort_kind

Process called "unique" that takes ar as NDArray.NDArray and return_index as Optional[Boolean] and return_inverse as Optional[Boolean] and return_counts as Optional[Boolean] and axis as Optional[Integer] returns UniqueResult:
    Let ret_index be return_index or false
    Let ret_inverse be return_inverse or false
    Let ret_counts be return_counts or false
    Return NDArray.unique with array as ar and return_index as ret_index and return_inverse as ret_inverse and return_counts as ret_counts and axis as axis

Type called "UniqueResult":
    values as NDArray.NDArray
    indices as Optional[NDArray.NDArray]
    inverse as Optional[NDArray.NDArray]
    counts as Optional[NDArray.NDArray]

Process called "searchsorted" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and v as NDArray.NDArray and side as Optional[String] and sorter as Optional[NDArray.NDArray] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let search_side be side or "left"
    Return NDArray.searchsorted with sorted_array as a and values as v and side as search_side and sorter as sorter

Note: Linear algebra functions (delegating to LinAlg module)
Process called "dot" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return LinAlg.dot with a as a and b as b

Process called "matmul" that takes x1 as NDArray.NDArray and x2 as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return LinAlg.matmul with a as x1 and b as x2

Process called "inner" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return LinAlg.inner with a as a and b as b

Process called "outer" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return LinAlg.outer with a as a and b as b

Process called "cross" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray and axisa as Optional[Integer] and axisb as Optional[Integer] and axisc as Optional[Integer] and axis as Optional[Integer] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return LinAlg.cross with a as a and b as b and axis as axis

Process called "trace" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and offset as Optional[Integer] and axis1 as Optional[Integer] and axis2 as Optional[Integer] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let diag_offset be offset or 0
    Let ax1 be axis1 or 0
    Let ax2 be axis2 or 1
    Return LinAlg.trace with matrix as a and offset as diag_offset and axis1 as ax1 and axis2 as ax2

Note: Array indexing and selection
Process called "where" that takes condition as NDArray.NDArray and x as Optional[NDArray.NDArray] and y as Optional[NDArray.NDArray] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    If x is not None and y is not None:
        Return NDArray.where with condition as condition and x as x and y as y
    Otherwise:
        Return NDArray.nonzero with array as condition

Process called "nonzero" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return NDArray.nonzero with array as a

Process called "take" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and indices as NDArray.NDArray and axis as Optional[Integer] and mode as Optional[String] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let take_axis be axis or 0
    Let index_mode be mode or "raise"
    Return NDArray.take with array as a and indices as indices and axis as take_axis and mode as index_mode

Process called "put" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and indices as NDArray.NDArray and values as NDArray.NDArray and mode as Optional[String]:
    Let index_mode be mode or "raise"
    NDArray.put with array as a and indices as indices and values as values and mode as index_mode

Process called "choose" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and choices as List[NDArray.NDArray] and mode as Optional[String] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let choice_mode be mode or "raise"
    Return NDArray.choose with indices as a and choices as choices and mode as choice_mode

Note: Input and output
Process called "save" that takes file as String and arr as NDArray.NDArray and allow_pickle as Optional[Boolean] and fix_imports as Optional[Boolean]:
    Let allow_pkl be allow_pickle or true
    NDArray.save_binary with filename as file and array as arr and compressed as false

Process called "load" that takes file as String and mmap_mode as Optional[String] and allow_pickle as Optional[Boolean] and fix_imports as Optional[Boolean] and encoding as Optional[String] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let allow_pkl be allow_pickle or true
    Return NDArray.load_binary with filename as file

Process called "savez" that takes file as String and arrays as List[NDArray.NDArray] and allow_pickle as Optional[Boolean] and fix_imports as Optional[Boolean]:
    Let allow_pkl be allow_pickle or true
    NDArray.save_compressed with filename as file and arrays as arrays

Process called "savez_compressed" that takes file as String and arrays as List[NDArray.NDArray] and allow_pickle as Optional[Boolean] and fix_imports as Optional[Boolean]:
    Let allow_pkl be allow_pickle or true
    NDArray.save_compressed with filename as file and arrays as arrays

Process called "savetxt" that takes fname as String and X as NDArray.NDArray and fmt as Optional[String] and delimiter as Optional[String] and newline as Optional[String] and header as Optional[String] and footer as Optional[String] and comments as Optional[String] and encoding as Optional[String]:
    Let format_str be fmt or "%.18e"
    Let delim be delimiter or " "
    NDArray.save_text with filename as fname and array as X and format as format_str and delimiter as delim

Process called "loadtxt" that takes fname as String and dtype as Optional[NDArray.DataType] and comments as Optional[String] and delimiter as Optional[String] and converters as Optional[Dictionary[Integer, Function[String, Any]]] and skiprows as Optional[Integer] and usecols as Optional[List[Integer]] and unpack as Optional[Boolean] and ndmin as Optional[Integer] and encoding as Optional[String] and max_rows as Optional[Integer] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let target_dtype be dtype or NDArray.Float64
    Let delim be delimiter or None
    Let skip_rows be skiprows or 0
    Return NDArray.load_text with filename as fname and dtype as target_dtype and delimiter as delim and skip_rows as skip_rows

Note: Random sampling (delegating to a random module)
Process called "random" that takes size as Optional[List[Integer]] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let shape be size or list containing 1
    Return generate_random_uniform with shape as shape and low as 0.0 and high as 1.0

Note: Utility functions
Process called "copy" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and order as Optional[String] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return NDArray.copy_array with arr as a

