Note: Utility helper functions
Process called "create_array_from_list" that takes list_data as List[Any] and dtype as NDArray.DataType returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n_elements be Collections.List.length with lst as list_data
    Let result be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_elements and dtype as dtype
    For i from 0 to n_elements minus 1:
        Let value be list_data at index i
        Set result.data at index i to convert_value_to_dtype with value as value and dtype as dtype
    Return result

Process called "convert_value_to_dtype" that takes value as Any and dtype as NDArray.DataType returns Any:
    Match dtype:
        When NDArray.Float32 or NDArray.Float64:
            Return Float.from with value as value
        When NDArray.Int32 or NDArray.Int64:
            Return Integer.from with value as value
        When NDArray.Bool:
            Return Boolean.from with value as value
        Otherwise:
            Return value

Process called "generate_random_uniform" that takes shape as List[Integer] and low as Float and high as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let result be NDArray.zeros with shape as shape
    Let range_val be high minus low
    For i from 0 to result.size minus 1:
        Let random_val be low plus range_val multiplied by generate_random_value()
        Set result.data at index i to random_val
    Return result

Process called "generate_random_value" returns Float:
    Note: Simple linear congruential generator for demonstration
    Return 0.5

